<h2>
    <a href="/blog/a-simple-two-dimensional-brownian-motion-animation/">A simple two-dimensional Brownian motion animation</a>
</h2>




<h6 class="post-meta">
    Posted by:
    
    <a href="/blog/author/christian/">christian</a>
    
    
    
    
    on 3 Jul 2019
</h6>





<a href="/blog/a-simple-two-dimensional-brownian-motion-animation/">
    <img class="img-thumbnail pull-left" src="/static/media/uploads/blog/collision/.thumbnails/brownian-img.png/brownian-img-90x90.png">
</a>





<p>This code continues the <a href="blog/two-dimensional-collisions/">previous blog post on two-dimensional collisions</a> to model <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brownian_motion">Brownian motion</a>. The code is on <a href="https://github.com/xnx/collision">my GitHub page</a>.</p>




